<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tropical Storm Iris and its 60 mph winds swirled in
the Atlantic as Hurricane Hugo devasted the eastern Caribbean.
   Iris' further strengthening was unlikely through this evening,
according to hurricane specialist Gil Clark of the National
Hurricane Center in suburban Coral Gables.
   Even so, the governments of Barbados, St. Vincent and St. Lucia
issued warnings for Iris, the ninth named storm of the Atlantic
hurricane season, which ends in November. Forecasters warned
residents of the Leeward Islands, raked by Hugo, to keep an eye on
Iris.
